Title: Konishi anomaly and N=1 effective superpotentials from matrix models

Comments: Latex, 8 pages, misprint and the normalization of the condensate in

the elliptic model are correctedJournal-ref: Phys.Lett. B554 (2003) 185-189

We discuss the restrictions imposed by the Konishi anomaly on the matrixmodel approach to the calculation of the effective superpotentials in N=1 SUSYgauge theories with different matter content. It is shown that they correspondto the anomaly deformed Virasoro $L_0$ constraints .